Real talk today, being an entrepreneur is like walking a tightrope, but add kidney failure into the mix, and it feels like a full-blown circus.

Living with kidney failure the last 3 years has thrown some unexpected curveballs my way, but it hasn’t stopped me from chasing my dreams. Balancing the demands of running a business while managing my health has been a hard, but I’m determined to keep the show going! 

Some days it feels like a juggling act. Appointments, treatments, procedures, hospital stays and medications alongside meetings, deadlines, and endless to-do lists. But hey, life is all about embracing challenges and finding the peace in the chaos.

Here’s what I’ve learned along the way. First: self-care is everything. Taking care of my physical and mental health is non-negotiable.

Second: don’t try to be Superman. Be honest with friends, family and clients. They cheer me on, help out and remind me that I’m not alone. 

Third: perspective is key. Dealing with kidney failure has given me a new appreciation for every small victory and milestone achieved.  I celebrate all the wins, big and small. It’s taught me to find joy in the simple things and celebrate my resilience. 

Embrace the chaos and keep working toward your goals. 

#EntrepreneurLife #charmingcharlton #houstonphotographer

3 tips to guarantee your photo shoot is a success as a music artist.

1. Plan and prepare the concept, location, props, and wardrobe that align with your brand identity. Create a mood board or visual references with your photographer or creative team to make sure everyone is on the same page.

2. Choose an experienced photographer who understands your genre and style. Take a look at their portfolio to make sure they’re familiar with working with musicians. You want your images to capture your personality, style and emotion.

3. Be authentic, expressive, and open to trying different poses and expressions during the shoot. Let your passion for music come through in the images.

Always communicate throughout the process. Review the images during the session and make adjustments if needed. This should get you the desired results.

Hello, I am formally known as Charming Charlton, a professional photographer here in Houston Texas. If you know me, personally, then you know, it’s not the norm for me to share my business, as I am an extremely private person. For years, I have suffered from severe heart and kidney failure. This has caused me to be in and out of the hospital from dizziness, short breath, heart issues, severe anxiety, muscle spasms and a list of other painful things. I have suffered in silence from kidney dialysis but I’ve reached a point in life where a kidney transplant is crucial to saving my life.  Asking for help, took a lot of courage and hurt my pride but I believe that my life is worth fighting for! Medical expenses for me are officially through the roof. I am leaning on my community to help me through this traumatic time. Please and thank you.
 
Link in my bio.

I wanted to take time out to thank everyone who has supported me throughout this process. It has been the hardest thing I’ve faced physically, emotionally and spiritually. People close to me understand what that hard looks like. 
I’m so grateful for all of the donations, kidney donor applicants, prayers, and photographers who have stepped in to shoot and edit for me during hospitals stays for nothing in return. It means everything because it kept me going.

With that being said I ask everyone to please keep sharing and donating what you can to help me reach my goal. 
***The link is in my bio if you would like to donate.***

I am still going, still shooting and booking so don’t pull back on that. I know a lot of people thought I was not accepting bookings or wanted me to rest but it helps me more for you to continue to support and shoot. 
Thank you 
-Charm
